00:12:16,000 --> 00:12:22,000
Pir kevin e. Û ev gund Hemkullekan...
 
It's very old. And this village, Hemkullekan...

107
00:12:22,000 --> 00:12:30,000
em gişt malek in. Em gişt ji Hemkullekan e. Berê ev gund,
şeş-heft mal e, em gişt ji wê bavî ne.
 
we are all one family. We are all Hemkullekan. Earlier, this
village was six-seven families, we are all from that father.

108
00:12:30,000 --> 00:12:39,000
Lê belê noka, kuniyetên me pir bûne. Ev jî kê wekir?
Hikûmetê wekir û zemanê Osmaniyan de wekirin.
 
However, now, our surnames have become many. And who did
this? The government did it, and they did it during the
Ottoman times.

109
00:12:39,000 --> 00:12:44,000
Ne me red kir. Mesele, maliyên Hemkullekan, kuniyetê me bû
Topal Hemo.
 
Not that we rejected it. For example, the families of
Hemkullekan, our surname became Topal Hemo.

110
00:12:44,000 --> 00:12:50,000
Topal Hemo, yanî di zemanê Tirkan de, Hemkullek seqet bû,
Topal Hemo.
 
Topal Hemo, meaning in the time of the Turks, Hemkullek was
disabled, Topal Hemo.

111
00:12:50,000 --> 00:12:54,000
Topal Hemo yanî seqet bû. Lê navê wî Hemkullek e.
 
Topal Hemo means he was disabled. But his name is Hemkullek.

112
00:12:54,000 --> 00:13:00,000
Bi Kurmancî em dibêjin Hemkullek. Naho jî em kirine çar-pênc
kuniyet.
 
In Kurmanji we say Hemkullek. And now they have made us
four-five surnames.

113
00:13:00,000 --> 00:13:07,000
Ya xî ev kuniyet pir çêbûne di nav me de, em gişt Hemkullek
in. Em gişt jî mervê hev in.
 
Brother, these surnames have become many among us, we are
all Hemkullek. We are all relatives.

114
00:13:07,000 --> 00:13:13,000
Xêr e, ev pênc-şeş kuniyet ê di nav me de, me di xwest û em
di xwazin, gişt bikê yek kuniyet ba.
 
Anyway, these five-six surnames among us, we wanted and we
want them all to be one surname.

115
00:13:13,000 --> 00:13:22,000
Gişt bi kuniyek ba. Paşê em ji de û çardeh-pazdeh bavan de
li vî welatî ne, ji mêj de.
 
All of them to be one surname. Then, we have been in this
country for fourteen-fifteen generations, for a long time.

116
00:13:22,000 --> 00:13:28,000
Domer heye, Înal heye, Mistefa heye, Xelîlbaş heye,
 
There is Domer, there is Înal, there is Mistefa, there is
Xelîlbaş,

117
00:13:28,000 --> 00:13:37,000
Hebîb heye, Osman heye. Paşê Hemkullek tê, yanî Hemkullek ji
sed û pêncî salî vir de ye.
 
There is Hebîb, there is Osman. Then comes Hemkullek,
meaning Hemkullek is from one hundred and fifty years ago.

118
00:13:37,000 --> 00:13:45,000
Lê meselê me pir ji mêj e, ji sêsed-çarsed salî de em xozan
in, yanî koka me li vir bû.
 
But our history is from a long time ago, we are elders from
three hundred-four hundred years ago, meaning our roots were
here.

119
00:13:45,000 --> 00:13:51,000
Em ji Hemkullek in, ev gund gişt em ji Hemkullek in. Ne ev
gund tenê.
 
We are from Hemkullek, this whole village, we are from
Hemkullek. Not just this village alone.

120
00:13:51,000 --> 00:13:57,000
No gundê E'lkê heye, ew jî Hemkullek in. Ew jî pismamên me
ne.
 
Now there is the village of E'lkê, they are also Hemkullek.
They are also our cousins.

121
00:13:57,000 --> 00:14:03,000
Ew jî pismamê me ne, no sê apê me li gundê E'lkê ne. Gundê
E'lkê jî yê me bû.
 
They are also our cousins, now we have three uncles in the
village of E'lkê. The village of E'lkê was also ours.

122
00:14:03,000 --> 00:14:06,000
Ew rojê ku em çûbûn em mêvanê wî gundî jî, me bername li wê
derê jî çêkir.
 
The day we went, we were guests in that village as well, we
made a program there too.

123
00:14:06,000 --> 00:14:08,000
Erê nê, pismamên me ne ev na. Lê apê me li wer in.
 
Yes, they are our cousins. But our uncles are there.

124
00:14:08,000 --> 00:14:11,000
Ez zanibim Serî Kaniyê jî ji pismamên we ne.
 
As far as I know, Serî Kaniyê is also your cousin's village.

125
00:14:11,000 --> 00:14:13,000
Serî Kaniyê jî pismamên me ne.
 
Serî Kaniyê are also our cousins.

126
00:14:13,000 --> 00:14:21,000
Serî Kaniyê, Hemdûş û Hemkullek birakê hev bûn. Hemdûş û
Hemkullek birakê hev bûn.
 
Serî Kaniyê, Hemdûş and Hemkullek were brothers. Hemdûş and
Hemkullek were brothers.

127
00:14:21,000 --> 00:14:26,000
Na ev bûn, ra dibêjin Hemdûşî, me ra dibêjin Hemkullekî. Lê
Hemdûş û Hemkullek birakê hev bûn, birakê hev bûn.
 
Now they are called Hemdûşî, and we are called Hemkullekî.
But Hemdûş and Hemkullek were brothers, they were brothers.

128
00:14:26,000 --> 00:14:30,000
Hemdûşî li Kefercenê man, em jî li vederê ne.
 
The Hemdûşî stayed in Kefercenê, and we are in Vederê.

129
00:14:30,000 --> 00:14:32,000
Navê gund jî aw qewirîn Serî Kaniyê bû?
 
Was the name of the village also changed to Serî Kaniyê?

130
00:14:32,000 --> 00:14:35,000
Lê. Berê em çûçik bûn. Kesî negot Kefercenê.
 
Yes. Previously, we were small. Nobody called it Kefercenê.

131
00:14:35,000 --> 00:14:41,000
Gişta digot çi? Emê biçin Serî Kaniyê. Em diçûn Serî Kaniyê.
 
What did everybody say? "We will go to Serî Kaniyê." We used
to go to Serî Kaniyê.

132
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:48,000
Em qeçik bûn, çûçik bûn hinga. Jin ka diçûn Serî Kaniyê
wilo, çirê ku av li gund kêm bû.
 
We were kids, small ones then. The women would go to Serî
Kaniyê like that, because water was scarce in the village.

133
00:14:48,000 --> 00:14:54,000
Kaniyê jî li nava baxçên belek bû. Cilên xwe, tiştên xwe
dibirin li wir dişûştin.
 
And the spring was in the middle of the gardens. They took
their clothes and belongings and washed them there.

134
00:14:54,000 --> 00:14:56,000
Li wir ziya dikirin.
 
They did their washing there.

135
00:14:56,000 --> 00:14:57,000
Ew jî evqasî nêzîkê hev in?
 
And they are this close to each other?

136
00:14:57,000 --> 00:15:00,000
E le, ev e, gî kîlometrek e mabêna me û Kefercenê.
 
Yes, it is about a kilometer between us and Kefercenê.

137
00:15:00,000 --> 00:15:03,000
Gî kîlometrek e. Em gelekî pir nêzîk in.
 
It's just a kilometer. We are very close.

138
00:15:03,000 --> 00:15:05,000
Gelo ka kîjan gundên mervên we ne mervê we ne?
 
I wonder which other villages have your relatives?

139
00:15:05,000 --> 00:15:14,000
Mervên me, xirabê şera, qismekî mezin têde mervên me ne. Na
dibêjin Mistêko. Dibêjin Mistêko. Em naho ji Mistefê de ji
me qetîne.
 
Our relatives, in Xirabê Şera, a large part of them are our
relatives. Now they call them Mistêko. They call them
Mistêko. Now we have separated from Mistefa.

140
00:15:14,000 --> 00:15:22,000
Malên hene li Xirêbê de, qismekî mezin. Bes ji mêj de ji me
qetîne. Na dibêjin Xelbaşo. Ji Xelîlbaş de ji me qetîne.
 
There are families in Xirêbe, a large part. But they have
separated from us a long time ago. Now they are called
Xelbaşo. They separated from us starting with Xelîlbaş.

141
00:15:22,000 --> 00:15:32,000
Û pir hene, ji mêj de ji me qetîne. Bes ê naho tevrî, ji me
re ne nêzîk mayî, em û Hemdûşan e. Hemdûş û Hemkullekî yekî
bi nav gotî, birakê hev bûn.
 
And there are many, who separated from us a long time ago.
But the ones now, the most closely related to us, are us and
the Hemdûş. Hemdûş and Hemkullek were, as named, brothers.

142
00:15:32,000 --> 00:15:38,000
Mesele wusa ye yanî.
 
This is the story, basically.

143
00:15:38,000 --> 00:15:40,000
Inha gundê we çiqasî dixwîne? Çend mal têde hene?
 
Now, what is the population of your village? How many houses
are there?

144
00:15:40,000 --> 00:15:41,000
Teqrîben dora hefteyê malî heye.
 
There are approximately around seventy houses.

145
00:15:41,000 --> 00:15:45,000
Hefteyê malî heye. Û em giş jî ji wê bavî ne.
 
There are seventy houses. And we are all from that father.

146
00:15:45,000 --> 00:15:49,000
Gelek ji gund derketin derve? Yanî mesele wek çûne Efrînê,
çûne derên din?
 
Did many leave the village? For instance, like going to
Afrin, going to other places?

147
00:15:49,000 --> 00:16:01,000
Erê hene, hene. Hene li Efrînê rûniştine, malên xwe li vir
jî hene. Û hene wextiyekê li Heleb bûn, bes milkê xwe û
malên xwe li vir hiştibûn.
 
Yes, there are. There are those living in Afrin, they have
their houses here too. And there were some who lived in
Aleppo for a while, but they had left their properties and
houses here.

148
00:16:01,000 --> 00:16:12,000
Yên hebûn, di wezîfê de bûn. Li Helebê rûniştî bûn. Yanî ev
e gengeşe, karê gengeşe. Yên Efrînê de, dikanên xwe hebûn,
derê xwe hebûn, bes... malên xwe...
 
There were those who were employed. They lived in Aleppo.
Meaning, it's about business. The ones in Afrin had their
shops, their places, but... their homes...

149
00:16:12,000 --> 00:16:18,000
Yanî hem li gund hene, û hem jî li bajar hene.
 
Meaning they are both in the village, and also in the city.

150
00:16:18,000 --> 00:16:21,000
No gundê we bi du navan tê naskirin, Me'rskê û gundê Ûsiv?
 
Now your village is known by two names, Me'rskê and the
village of Ûsiv?

151
00:16:21,000 --> 00:16:22,000
Ev navê Ûsiv ji ku hatiye?
 
Where did the name Ûsiv come from?

152
00:16:22,000 --> 00:16:31,000
Ûsiv... Ne me got Ûsiv û Xelîl birakê hev bûn. Birakê hev
bûn, du birak bûn. Du gunda xwe hebûn.
 
Ûsiv... Didn't we say Ûsiv and Xelîl were brothers. They
were brothers, there were two brothers. They had two
villages.

153
00:16:31,000 --> 00:16:40,000
Ûsiv li Me'rskê rûnişt, Xelîl jî li gundê E'lkê rûnişt. Em
dibên gundê E'lkê.
 
Ûsiv stayed in Me'rskê, Xelîl also stayed in the village of
E'lkê. We call it the village of E'lkê.

154
00:16:40,000 --> 00:16:45,000
Ûsiv li vî derê, ode vekir, odeyê mîvano.
 
Ûsiv opened a room here, a guest room.

155
00:16:45,000 --> 00:16:47,000
Berê li her gundekî odekê mîvano hebû?
 
Did every village have a guest room back then?

156
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:49,000
E, odeyê mîvano hebû. Berê wekî nahû, makîneyê dar birinê
nebûn.
 
Yes, there was a guest room. Back then, it wasn't like now,
there were no tree-cutting machines.

157
00:16:49,000 --> 00:17:00,000
Berê ev du gundî, ra merîk derbas bû gihaştiye vî derî,
hêvar dibû, ê ku derê here? Digot kî em ê...? Em ê eyan
odayê. Em ê bixwin û em ê vexin û em ê xewkin. Em ê sibehê
da taştê xwe jî bixwin, û em ê lêxin herin ciyê ku em pê
herin.
 
In the past, if a person from two villages over passed by
and arrived here, and evening fell, where would they go?
They would say, "Where will we...?" "We'll go to the room.
We'll eat, drink, and sleep. We'll eat our breakfast in the
morning, and then we'll hit the road to wherever we're
going."

158
00:17:00,000 --> 00:17:11,000
Berê weha bû yanî. Û Ûsiv xwedî dêwan bû. Yanî rehmet lêkê,
Ûsiv, Hecî Ûsiv, xwedî dêwan bû.
 
It used to be like that. And Ûsiv was the host of a diwan. I
mean, God rest his soul, Ûsiv, Hecî Ûsiv, was the host of a
diwan.

159
00:17:11,000 --> 00:17:14,000
Yanî bi wê, ê xwe derket.
 
That's how he became known.

160
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:22,000
Naho mentîqe der û dora Efrînê, pirraniyê berê dibêjin gundê
Me'rskê, lê gundê Ûsiv?
 
Now the region around Afrin, do the majority of people refer
to it as the village of Me'rskê, or the village of Ûsiv?

161
00:17:22,000 --> 00:17:31,000
Ne, ne, pirr dibêjin Me'rskê. Bes va gundê nêzîkî me der û
dora we, ê qismek jê dibê gundê Ûsiv. Xêr e le, navê Ûsiv di
vî gundî de mafî, û ha xudanê gund bû.
 
No, no, they mostly say Me'rskê. But these villages close to
us, around us, a part of them call it the village of Ûsiv.
Anyway, the name of Ûsiv remained in this village, and he
was the owner of the village.

162
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:34,000
Erê, wisa bû.
 
Yes, that's how it was.

163
00:17:34,000 --> 00:17:44,000
Gundê we jî di sînorê... bi navbera Efrînê û herêma Şehbayê
da ye. Gelek êrîş jî hatin ser we di vê şoreşê de?
 
Your village is on the border... between Afrin and the
Shahba region. There have been many attacks on you during
this revolution, haven't there?

164
00:17:44,000 --> 00:17:56,000
E, le êrîş sê caran hatin ser me. Me ji gund derneketin.
Dawêrtin me, me da wêrt wan, derdiketin...
 
Yes, well, we were attacked three times. We didn't leave the
village. They fired at us, we fired back at them, they
left...

165
00:17:56,000 --> 00:18:08,000
Yekcaran yekcaran me digot jin û ji gund derxin, qeçkê çûçik
derxin. Em mêr di gund de diman, em der neketin. Em qet
derneketin. Ebeden em derneketin.
 
Sometimes, occasionally, we'd say "Take the women out of the
village, take the small children out." We men stayed in the
village, we didn't leave. We never left. We absolutely
didn't leave.

166
00:18:08,000 --> 00:18:20,000
Û elhemdulellah em serketin, û reva çûn. E, le çend şehîd
ketin, çûn. Bes ciwan jî...
 
And thank God, we prevailed, and they fled. Yes, well, some
fell as martyrs, they passed away. But the youth...

167
00:18:20,000 --> 00:18:33,000
Çar caran bi qasiyê me ketin yanî çûn. Û reva çûn. Û neha jî
em di wê derê de, weha...
 
Four times they got to our size, I mean, they went. And they
ran away. And right now we are in that place, like this...

168
00:18:33,000 --> 00:18:35,000
Em musaytir in yanî.
 
We are in control, basically.

169
00:18:35,000 --> 00:18:44,000
Mamo we qebê, xwedê kê masiyê we nede. Saeta te xweş. Ehlen
û sehlen jî hatina we, û em kêfxweş dibin. Û em dixwazin hûn
tim herin werin cem me.
 
Uncle, may God bless you, may God not let anything bad
happen to you. Have a good time. Welcome, and we are happy.
And we want you to always come visit us.

170
00:18:44,000 --> 00:18:45,000
Inşallah em ê tim werin nê.
 
God willing, we will always come.

171
00:18:45,000 --> 00:18:47,000
Ser çavan, hun ser çavan.
 
You are welcome, you are welcome.

172
00:18:47,000 --> 00:19:00,000
Spas ji te ra.
 
Thank you.

173
00:19:00,000 --> 00:19:12,000
Gundê Me'rskê girêdayî navçeya Şera ya Kantona Efrînê 12
kîlometreyî li başûrê rojhilatê navçeya Şera û 17
kîlometreyî li rohilatê bajarê Efrînê dikeve.
 
The village of Me'rskê is affiliated with the Shera district
of the Afrin Canton, located 12 kilometers to the southeast
of the Shera district and 17 kilometers to the east of the
city of Afrin.

174
00:19:12,000 --> 00:19:22,000
Navê gund ji wateya "Me'serê", ango "Kuvaşk"ê hatiye. Ji ber
ku gelek kuvaşgehên tirî di gund de hebûn û ev nav lê hatiye
kirin.
 
The name of the village comes from the meaning of "Me'serê"
(winepress), that is, "Kuvaşk". Because there were many
grape presses in the village, and it was given this name.

175
00:19:22,000 --> 00:19:30,000
Derdora gund bi dar û beran e, û hewş û xaniyên gund bi gul
û çîçek û darên curebicure n.
 
The surroundings of the village are full of trees and
bushes, and the courtyards and houses of the village have
various flowers, blossoms, and trees.

176
00:19:30,000 --> 00:19:40,000
Di her malekê de hemû cureyên çîçek û gulan tên dîtin. Ev
xuyadeke ku xelkên gund gelekî ji çandiniyê, xweza, û
xemlandinê hez dikin.
 
In every home, all types of blossoms and flowers can be
seen. This shows that the village people very much love
farming, nature, and decoration.

177
00:19:40,000 --> 00:19:56,000
Hemkullek kesê yekemîn e ku di gund de niştecih bûye. Lewma
hemû malbatên gund bi malbata Hemkullek têne naskirin, û ew
birayê Hemdoş bû, ku li Kefercenê niştecih bûye.
 
Hemkulê was the first person to settle in the village.
Therefore, all the families of the village are known by the
Hemkulê family, and he was the brother of Hemdûş, who
settled in Kefercenê.

178
00:19:56,000 --> 00:20:00,000
Hemû niştecihên gund ji yek malbatî ne, ango malbata
Hemkullek...
 
All the inhabitants of the village are from one family,
namely the Hemkullek...

179
00:20:00,000 --> 00:20:03,000
Golek ji eşîra Şikakan e,
 
A branch of the Shikak tribe,

180
00:20:03,000 --> 00:20:06,000
Her wisa navê malbata han ku yek ji li gund e
 
Likewise, the name of this family, which is one of the
families in the village,

181
00:20:06,000 --> 00:20:09,000
El Kêcî, nişteciyê gund in
 
El Kêcî, they are residents of the village

182
00:20:09,000 --> 00:20:11,000
Û li wir dijîn.
 
And live there.

183
00:20:11,000 --> 00:20:13,000
Gundê me, rûbera wî ne mezin e,
 
Our village, its area is not large,

184
00:20:13,000 --> 00:20:15,000
Lê hewşên wan mezin û fereh in.
 
But their courtyards are large and spacious.

185
00:20:15,000 --> 00:20:18,000
Lewma tenê nêzî heştê xanî
 
Therefore, there are only about eighty houses

186
00:20:18,000 --> 00:20:24,000
Û derdora hefsed kes li gund dijîn.
 
And around seven hundred people live in the village.

187
00:20:24,000 --> 00:20:27,000
Li bakurê gund, serê kaniyê,
 
In the north of the village, at the head of the spring,

188
00:20:27,000 --> 00:20:30,000
Rûniştgehekî kevnar e, başûr û şerq El Coz,
 
There is an ancient settlement, to the south and east is El
Joz,

189
00:20:30,000 --> 00:20:32,000
Û rojava gundê Kefermezê,
 
And to the west is the village of Kafermez,

190
00:20:32,000 --> 00:20:34,000
Û Meşaleyê ne.
 
And Mashalah.

191
00:20:34,000 --> 00:20:38,000
Hemû herêmên derdora gund deşt e, û axa wî sor e,
 
All the areas around the village are plains, and its soil is
red,

192
00:20:38,000 --> 00:20:41,000
Û ji bo çandiniyê gelekî dewlemend e.
 
And it is very rich for agriculture.

193
00:20:41,000 --> 00:20:45,000
Hêjayî gotinê ye ku çiyayê Lêlûnê ji vî gundî dest pê dike,
 
It is worth mentioning that the Mount Lelun starts from this
village,

194
00:20:45,000 --> 00:20:48,000
Û ta deşta Cûmê didome.
 
And continues until the Jume plain.

195
00:20:48,000 --> 00:20:52,000
Li rojavayê gund kaniyek, bi navê Kaniya Kevan, heye.
 
In the west of the village, there is a spring called the
Spring of the Bows.

196
00:20:52,000 --> 00:20:55,000
Ji ber ku gelek kew li derdora wê diciviyan,
 
Because many partridges used to gather around it,

197
00:20:55,000 --> 00:20:58,000
Û nêçîrvanan li wir nêçîra kewan dikirin,
 
And hunters used to hunt partridges there,

198
00:20:58,000 --> 00:21:00,000
Û ta niha ev kaniye heye.
 
And this spring exists to this day.

199
00:21:00,000 --> 00:21:03,000
Xwezaya vî cihî gellekî xweş e, û seyrangehek e.
 
The nature of this place is very beautiful, and it's a
picnic area.

200
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:07,000
Gundî di werzên bihar û havînê de seredana wê dikin,
 
The villagers visit it during the spring and summer seasons,

201
00:21:07,000 --> 00:21:23,000
Û rojên xweş lê derbas dikin.
 
And spend pleasant days there.

202
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:25,000
Mamoste Mihemed, merheba ji te re.
 
Teacher Mihemed, hello to you.

203
00:21:25,000 --> 00:21:27,000
Ehlen we sehlen, ser çava, bixêr hatin.
 
Welcome, upon my eyes, you are welcome.

204
00:21:27,000 --> 00:21:31,000
Sax bî. Em derbasî serê gundê we bûn, me meraq kir ku em
derbasî dibistanê jî bibin.
 
Be healthy. We entered the beginning of your village, we
were curious to visit the school as well.

205
