living for their families.

332
00:31:56,000 --> 00:32:07,000
Bêhtirî şêniyên gund jin û mêr karmend in. Di saziyên û
dezgehên Rêveberiya Xweser da, li bajarokê Keferşerayê û
bajarê Efrînê dixebitin.
 
Most of the villagers, men and women, are civil servants.
They work in the institutions and agencies of the Autonomous
Administration, in the town of Keferşera and the city of
Afrin.

333
00:32:07,000 --> 00:32:16,000
Ev gund weke gundê rewşenbîran tê binavkirin. Ji ber ku
rêjeya rewşenbîr û xwendevanan ji mêr û jinan di gund da
gelekî bilind e.
 
This village is known as the village of intellectuals.
Because the rate of intellectuals and students among men and
women in the village is very high.

334
00:32:16,000 --> 00:32:21,000
Û bêhtirî sed kesî zanîngeh di beşên curebicure da
qedandine.
 
And more than a hundred people have graduated from
university in various departments.

335
00:32:21,000 --> 00:32:28,000
Hêjayî gotinê ye ku dibistana gund a lîseyê, Yûnîsêfê di
sala 1985an da ava bûye.
 
It is worth mentioning that the village's high school, was
built by UNICEF in 1985.

336
00:32:28,000 --> 00:32:42,000
Û ew yek ji pênc dibistanên Sûriyê ku ji aliyê vê rêxistinê
ve ava bûye.
 
And it is one of the five schools in Syria that was built by
this organization.

337
00:32:42,000 --> 00:32:49,000
Gund ji sala 2013an ta destpêka 2016an rastî êrîşên hemû
grûbên çeteyan hatine.
 
The village faced attacks from all mercenary groups from
2013 to the beginning of 2016.

338
00:32:49,000 --> 00:32:58,000
Lê tu carî wan serê xwe netewandin û li nik hêzên YPG û YPJ
çeperên gundê xwe parastin.
 
But they never bowed their heads and alongside the YPG and
YPJ forces, they defended their village's trenches.

339
00:32:58,000 --> 00:33:05,000
Bi vê awayî ropela pakiş ji berxwedanî û qehremaniyê di
pirtûka dîrokê da nivîsandin.
 
In this way, they wrote a clean page of resistance and
heroism in the history book.

340
00:33:05,000 --> 00:33:11,000
Sê pakrewanên gund hene ku di têkoşîna rizgariya netewî ya
Kurdistanê da şehîd bûne.
 
The village has three martyrs who were martyred in the
national liberation struggle of Kurdistan.

341
00:33:11,000 --> 00:33:15,000
Û bûn e sembola azadî û serfiraziyê.
 
And they became the symbol of freedom and victory.

342
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:21,000
Wêneyên şehîd Ebo, Sêwas, Amed, Amanos li nava gund
daliqandine.
 
Pictures of martyrs Ebo, Sêwas, Amed, Amanos are hung in the
village.

343
00:33:21,000 --> 00:33:34,000
Komîna gund bi navê şehîd Sêwas hatiye binavkirin.
 
The village commune has been named after martyr Sêwas.

344
00:33:34,000 --> 00:33:38,000
Belê temaşevanan, hêja. Îro em li gundê Me'riskê ne.
 
Yes, esteemed viewers. Today we are in the village of
Me'riskê.

345
00:33:38,000 --> 00:33:42,000
Tiştekî bala min kişand, dimeşim, çavê me li firfirkekê ket.
 
Something caught my attention as I was walking, we saw a
pinwheel.

346
00:33:42,000 --> 00:33:44,000
Merheba ji we ra.
 
Hello to you.

347
00:33:44,000 --> 00:33:45,000
Ehlen û sehlen pismam.
 
Welcome, cousin.

348
00:33:45,000 --> 00:33:46,000
Qewet be.
 
More power to you.

349
00:33:46,000 --> 00:33:47,000
Sax bî ehlen û sehlen.
 
Be well, welcome.

350
00:33:47,000 --> 00:33:48,000
Em te nas bikin?
 
Can we know you?

351
00:33:48,000 --> 00:33:49,000
Mistefa Ehmed ji Me'riskê me.
 
I am Mistefa Ehmed, from Me'riskê.

352
00:33:49,000 --> 00:33:51,000
Wey li ser çavên min. Çavê te sax bin.
 
Oh, upon my eyes. May your eyes be well.

353
00:33:51,000 --> 00:33:52,000
Ev avê dikşîne, ne?
 
Is this drawing water?

354
00:33:52,000 --> 00:33:55,000
Avê dikşîne, li ser bîrê me rakiriye, wilo avê dikşîne.
 
It draws water, we installed it on the well, it draws water
like this.

355
00:33:55,000 --> 00:33:57,000
Em pê darên xwe av didin.
 
We water our trees with it.

356
00:33:57,000 --> 00:34:00,000
Ev ji ber bayê ye? Ev bi qûweta bayê av didê...
 
Is this from the wind? It waters by the power of the wind...

357
00:34:00,000 --> 00:34:02,000
Bi ser bayê dixebite. Erê.
 
It works by the wind. Yes.

358
00:34:02,000 --> 00:34:03,000
Ev bîr ev e ku berê da hebû ye?
 
Was this well here before?

359
00:34:03,000 --> 00:34:10,000
Na me kolaye bîr... Berê bîrek li vê derê hebû, hewa hişk
bû, me ev der bû 2 sal in me kolaye.
 
No, we dug the well... There used to be a well here before,
it was a dry well, we dug this place 2 years ago.

360
00:34:10,000 --> 00:34:17,000
Me firfirka xwe anî, em li ser gund da çêkirin û me ava kir.
Em avê derdixînim, pê daran xwe av didin.
 
We brought our pinwheel, we made it in the village and built
it. We draw water with it, we water our trees with it.

361
00:34:17,000 --> 00:34:22,000
Em birka xwe tijî av dikin, û darên xwe pê av didin.
 
We fill our pool with water, and water our trees with it.

362
00:34:22,000 --> 00:34:24,000
Çiqas zeytûn erdê we hene li vir?
 
How many olives do you have on your land here?

363
00:34:24,000 --> 00:34:30,000
Ev darên zeytûnê hene, darên kerezan hene... çi qas dar
hene, em gişî av didin.
 
We have these olive trees, we have cherry trees... whatever
trees there are, we water them all.

364
00:34:30,000 --> 00:34:35,000
Ev ava ku tu dibêjî ev gund giştî ye... ev av e, ev gund
giştî dibe yan te tenê ye?
 
This water that you say is for the whole village... does the
whole village take this water or is it only yours?

365
00:34:35,000 --> 00:34:38,000
Ê me tenê ye, bes gund giş jê dibe.
 
It is only ours, but the whole village takes from it.

366
00:34:38,000 --> 00:34:46,000
Dema kehrebe tune be, paşî ava wê pir xweş e... miyanê çayê
nîvî gund te ji vir ava xwe dibe.
 
When there is no electricity, and its water is very good...
for tea, half of the village takes their water from here.

367
00:34:46,000 --> 00:34:52,000
Piranî ev bîr a ku dibêjin ava wê kils e... yanî ava wê ji
bo çayê nêtê vexwarinê.
 
Mostly, they say well water is calcified... meaning its
water isn't suitable for drinking for tea.

368
00:34:52,000 --> 00:34:53,000
Yanî ev ava we xweş e?
 
So your water is good?

369
00:34:53,000 --> 00:35:00,000
Rast e, heye wisa ye. Evê pir xweş e ava xwe. Evê kils tê da
tune ye. Ava xwe pir rind e... sihî ye.
 
It's true, there are some like that. Its water is very good.
There is no calcification in it. Its water is very nice...
it's healthy.

370
00:35:00,000 --> 00:35:04,000
Ê gund a din, ê pir kilsî, ava wê netê vexwarin...
 
Yeah, the other village's is very calcified, its house water
isn't suitable for drinking...

371
00:35:04,000 --> 00:35:13,000
Ji malên ra bes av didin. Bes ava me ne pir pak e ava xwe,
gund dûre... ji gund dûre erda xwe wisa ye jiber pak e ava
giştî pir pak e.
 
They only give water to the houses. But our water is not
very clean, its water... it is far from the village. Since
the land is far from the village, it's clean, the general
water is very clean.

372
00:35:13,000 --> 00:35:16,000
Ev çend sal e ev bîr hatiye çêkirin e?
 
How many years has this well been built?

373
00:35:16,000 --> 00:35:21,000
Bîr a kevn, bû sê sal in... Eva, bû 4 sal in, me ev bîr a
kolaye.
 
The old well, it's been three years... This one, it's been 4
years since we dug this well.

374
00:35:21,000 --> 00:35:24,000
Ev firfirka te wek kî çêkiriye ev... ev weke?
 
Who made this pinwheel of yours... this like?

375
00:35:24,000 --> 00:35:27,000
Rehmetê xudê lê be, loqiyê me çêkir.
 
The late, god's mercy on him, he made it.

376
00:35:27,000 --> 00:35:29,000
Min cara nedî, nav gundan min nedî, bes min?
 
I have never seen it before, I didn't see it in the
villages, but me?

377
00:35:29,000 --> 00:35:32,000
Tenê li mintaqeya me Efrînê gişê, tenê ew e... Îlla hebe bes
ev e.
 
Only in our region, in all of Afrin, it's only this... If
there is any, it's only this.

378
00:35:32,000 --> 00:35:34,000
Wekû xetên trênê jî hene?
 
Do we have train lines too?

379
00:35:34,000 --> 00:35:40,000
Belê... li giştî wekû... Li meydanê tune ye na. Bes ev e me
çêkiriye.
 
Yes... in general... There isn't any in the field, no. It's
only this that we made.

380
00:35:40,000 --> 00:35:43,000
Ê bavê te bi xwe çêkir, hîsinkar bû ya çi...
 
Oh, your father made it himself, was he a blacksmith or
what...

381
00:35:43,000 --> 00:35:46,000
Eh he, hîsinkar bû, erê. Bixwe çêkir, hîsinkar bû.
 
Yeah, he was a blacksmith, yes. He made it himself, he was a
blacksmith.

382
00:35:46,000 --> 00:35:48,000
Di kîjan salê de çêkir?
 
In what year did he make it?

383
00:35:48,000 --> 00:35:54,000
Di 80 de, sala 80 de, 82 bû... di van hudûdan de.
 
In the 80s, in the year 80, it was 82... around those
bounds.

384
00:35:54,000 --> 00:35:58,000
Eh, dema te xwe da çêkir... bes tiştekî pir hêja ye... Eh,
elektrîkê jî naxwaze...
 
Uh, when you had it made... but it is something very
valuable... Uh, it doesn't need electricity either...

385
00:35:58,000 --> 00:36:04,000
Kehrebê tiştekî naxwaze... Bes ba hebe û ceme jî. Menteqeya
me ba wê heye. Tem e, kane.
 
It doesn't need electricity or anything... Only if there is
wind and freezing. Our region has its wind. Always, there
is.

386
00:36:04,000 --> 00:36:07,000
Bayê wê tim nizamî ye, rind dixebite.
 
Its wind is always regular, it works well.

387
00:36:07,000 --> 00:36:11,000
Belê, bayê wê... tim nîzamî... rind dixebite, erê.
 
Yes, its wind... always regular... works well, yes.

388
00:36:11,000 --> 00:36:13,000
Em sipas dikin mala te ava be.
 
We thank you, may your house be built.

389
00:36:13,000 --> 00:36:21,000
Em spasiya we dikin, mala te ava be.
 
We thank you, may your house be built.

390
00:36:21,000 --> 00:36:30,000
Di hezîrana 2013an da artêşa Azad, Cebhet el Nusra, DAIŞ û
rêxistinên din, êrîşî gund kirin.
 
In June 2013, the Free Syrian Army, Al-Nusra Front, ISIS,
and other organizations attacked the village.

391
00:36:30,000 --> 00:36:35,000
Û xelkê gund bi alîkariya YPG û YPJ ketin sengerên şer.
 
And the people of the village entered the battle trenches
with the help of YPG and YPJ.

392
00:36:35,000 --> 00:36:38,000
Ji sedî 80yî jinên gund di malên xwe da neman.
 
80 percent of the women of the village did not stay in their
homes.

393
00:36:38,000 --> 00:36:40,000
Û çeka namûsê hildan.
 
And they took up the weapon of honor.

394
00:36:40,000 --> 00:36:44,000
Li kêleka mêran li dijî hêzên dijmin şer kirin.
 
They fought alongside the men against the enemy forces.

395
00:36:44,000 --> 00:36:50,000
Çeteyan hemû çekên giran li dijî gund bi kar anîn. Nêzîkî
sed top avêtin gund.
 
The mercenaries used all heavy weapons against the village.
They fired nearly a hundred shells at the village.

396
00:36:50,000 --> 00:36:53,000
Û şer do sê rojan berdewam kir.
 
And the war continued for two or three days.

397
00:36:53,000 --> 00:36:58,000
Di encamê de piştî şehadeta çar lehengên YPGê, çete reviyan.
 
In the end, after the martyrdom of four YPG heroes, the
mercenaries fled.

398
00:36:58,000 --> 00:37:00,000
Û nekarîbûn têkevin gund.
 
And they could not enter the village.

399
00:37:00,000 --> 00:37:03,000
Û şervanên YPGê bi pêş ketin.
 
And the YPG fighters advanced.

400
00:37:03,000 --> 00:37:07,000
Piştre hemû xelkê gund vegeriyan cih û warên xwe.
 
Afterwards, all the people of the village returned to their
places and homes.

401
00:37:07,000 --> 00:37:20,000
Û naha bi kêf û xweşî jiyana xwe berdewam dikin.
 
And now, with joy and happiness, they continue their lives.

402
00:37:20,000 --> 00:37:21,000
Merhaba jinbapê.
 
Welcome sister.

403
00:37:21,000 --> 00:37:23,000
Ehlen û sehlen.
 
Welcome.

404
00:37:23,000 --> 00:37:24,000
Em a nasbikin destpêkê?
 
Can we get to know you first?

405
00:37:24,000 --> 00:37:25,000
Navê min Xalîde ye.
 
My name is Xalîde.

406
00:37:25,000 --> 00:37:27,000
Ser çavan... dayê em navê te nasbikin?
 
Upon my eyes... mother, let me get to know your name?

407
00:37:27,000 --> 00:37:28,000
Fîdan e.
 
It's Fîdan.

408
00:37:28,000 --> 00:37:37,000
Ser çavê min... Dayê em dest pê bikin, da dest pê bikin.
E... we behsa xwarinekî kir, wekî xwarinekî bêtaybet di
gundê me da çêdikin.
 
Upon my eyes... Mother let's start, so we can start. Uh...
you mentioned a food, like a special food made in our
village.

409
00:37:37,000 --> 00:37:38,000
Erê.
 
Yes.

410
00:37:38,000 --> 00:37:41,000
Kanê tu bikarî navê wê xwarinê bêjî ji me ra. Navê xwarinê?
 
Can you tell us the name of that food. Name of the food?

411
00:37:41,000 --> 00:37:44,000
Ev xwarin a... navê xwarinê kebab keraz e.
 
This food... the name of the food is cherry kebab.

412
00:37:44,000 --> 00:37:51,000
Em goşt diqelînin, em didin... em nanê xwe jî diqelînin...
di safînin...
 
We roast the meat, we add it... we roast our bread too... we
strain it...

413
00:37:51,000 --> 00:37:59,000
Û em goz û behîvan jî diqelînin, didinê... û em esîrê...
kerazan jî... e xweş tenê..
 
and we also roast walnuts and almonds, we add them... and we
juice... the cherries too... it is very nice..

414
00:37:59,000 --> 00:38:00,000
Yanî avên din, tu av nadeyê nê?
 
So you don't add any other water, right?

415
00:38:00,000 --> 00:38:06,000
Na av e na. Me'ne xusûsî hev e. Me'ne şerabe ye û me'ne leçe
ye ev o, em pê çêdikin.
 
No, no water. I mean specifically it's like a wine and like
a syrup this is, we make it with it.

416
00:38:06,000 --> 00:38:11,000
Yanî baba kerazan e, ev xwarin a we jî bi kerazan e.
 
So it's cherry's essence, this food of yours is also with
cherries.

417
00:38:11,000 --> 00:38:14,000
Ê lê bi keraz bû. Nîştî me kir ez av e çêkim. Erê, rast e.
 
Yes, it was with cherries. We settled, I made the juice.
Yes, that's right.

418
00:38:14,000 --> 00:38:17,000
Ev xwarin a ji zû da çêdikin yan we dema kir da çêdikin?
 
Have you been making this food for a long time or when did
you start making it?

419
00:38:17,000 --> 00:38:20,000
Çaxê ku keraz di cem me çêbûn nê em çêdikin.
 
When cherries grew with us, then we make it.

420
00:38:20,000 --> 00:38:27,000
Ê lê berê mane nizanî bû. Çemê me çandin, gihaştin. Û em hîn
bûn me çêkir.
 
Yes, but before we didn't know. Our river, they planted,
they ripened. And we learned, we made it.

421
00:38:27,000 --> 00:38:31,000
Ev xwarina bêtaybet li ku derê çêdikin, yan kîjan bajar da
çêdikin?
 
Where specifically is this food made, or in which cities do
they make it?

422
00:38:31,000 --> 00:38:40,000
Ev xwarina Rîha çêdike, Heleb jî çêdikin. Rîha, ew jî Heleb
e. Rîha meşhûr e bi kerazan, ew jî... Î ev Helebî ye û ev
Rîhayî ye.
 
This food is made in Urfa, they make it in Aleppo too. Urfa
and Aleppo it is. Urfa is famous for cherries, that too...
Yes this is Aleppan and this is Urfan.

423
00:38:40,000 --> 00:38:42,000
Yanî ew jî eynî vê xwarinê wisa çêdikin?
 
So they also make this food exactly like this?

424
00:38:42,000 --> 00:38:45,000
Erê... de me ji wan ra kiriye.
 
Yes... we made it for them.

425
00:38:45,000 --> 00:38:50,000
Kanê ka yek yek bêje, ev nan e te qelandin?
 
Say them one by one, is this the bread you roasted?

426
00:38:50,000 --> 00:38:58,000
Ev nan e, me qelandin. Vêca em davêjine nava sehnê.
 
This is bread, we roasted it. Now we put it in the plate.

427
00:38:58,000 --> 00:39:18,000
Em vêga jî goşt têkin. Ev jî goşt e... erê. Me qelandî û em
davêjinê.
 
Now we will put the meat in. This is meat... yes. We roasted
it and we throw it in.

428
00:39:18,000 --> 00:39:38,000
Niha jî, em ê ava keraza tê kin e.
 
Now, we will pour in the cherry juice.

429
00:39:47,000 --> 00:39:49,000
Piştî wê...
 
After this...

430
00:39:49,000 --> 00:39:56,000
Piştî wê, em pextenûsê têkine.
 
After this, we add parsley.

431
00:39:56,000 --> 00:40:00,000
Ev jî behîv û goz.
 
This is almonds and walnuts.

432
00:40:00,000 --> 00:40:02,000
Hev a çi ne, me qewirme dît.
 
What are these, we saw the braised meat.

433
00:40:02,000 --> 00:40:04,000
Hev ji min qewirandin.
 
I roasted these too.

434
00:40:04,000 --> 00:40:15,000
Û hev jî kişane nanê da iser.
 
And this is poured over the bread.

435
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:16,000
Hev a hana cahiz bûn.
 
These ones were ready.

436
00:40:16,000 --> 00:40:17,000
Na ev hazir bûn.
 
No, these were ready.

437
00:40:17,000 --> 00:40:20,000
Ev hazir bûn. Eva hana ya ku we ra xwar dade.
 
These were ready. This is the one that you will eat.

438
00:40:20,000 --> 00:40:21,000
Te destpêkê heta çi qewirandin? ...Te di nav hev da kirî
qewirandin?
 
What did you roast at first? ...Did you roast them together?

439
00:40:21,000 --> 00:40:22,000
Min kir qewirme, erê.
 
I roasted them, yes.

440
00:40:22,000 --> 00:40:26,000
Mîsal ev goşt qewirme, paşê min nan qewirandin.
 
For example, this meat is braised, then I roasted the bread.

441
00:40:26,000 --> 00:40:27,000
Uh huh.
 
Uh huh.

442
00:40:27,000 --> 00:40:29,000
Paşê jî min goz û behîv qewirandin.
 
Then I also roasted walnuts and almonds.

443
00:40:29,000 --> 00:40:30,000
Uh huh.
 
Uh huh.

444
00:40:30,000 --> 00:40:33,000
Û min anî... min anî hana kir. Bextê me zêxwe ra jî hûr kir.
 
And I brought... I brought it and prepared it like this.
Luckily, I also chopped it for ourselves.

445
00:40:33,000 --> 00:40:34,000
Destê te sax bin.
 
Bless your hands.

446
00:40:34,000 --> 00:40:36,000
Wê jî sax bin, saheta we xwaş.
 
Bless yours too, good health to you.

447
00:40:36,000 --> 00:40:37,000
Spas.
 
Thank you.

448
00:40:37,000 --> 00:40:40,000
Spas te ra dayê.
 
Thank you, mother.

449
00:40:40,000 --> 00:40:41,000
Em werin cem te jî.
 
Let's come to you as well.

450
00:40:41,000 --> 00:40:44,000
Dayê em werin cem te.
 
Mother, let's come to you.

451
00:40:44,000 --> 00:40:45,000
Te jî...
 
You also...

452
00:40:45,000 --> 00:40:46,000
Te ji bo çi hazir kiriye?
 
What did you prepare?

453
00:40:46,000 --> 00:40:49,000
Min leçer hazir kiriye. Leçerê kêrazê.
 
I prepared leçer. Cherry leçer.

454
00:40:49,000 --> 00:40:51,000
Û çawa çêdikin, ka hinekî ji me ra bêje.
 
And how do they make it, tell us a little bit.

455
00:40:51,000 --> 00:40:56,000
Kêrazê leçer, evê mize, tirş e.
 
Leçer cherry, this is sour, it's tart.

456
00:40:56,000 --> 00:40:58,000
Ne ji yê xwarinê ye.
 
It's not the one for eating.

457
00:40:58,000 --> 00:41:01,000
Emê wînin werin dendikên wî derxînin.
 
We will bring it and remove its seeds.

458
00:41:01,000 --> 00:41:06,000
Emê kîlok şikir, kîlok û nîv kêrazê...
 
We add a kilo of sugar, a kilo and a half of cherries...

459
00:41:06,000 --> 00:41:07,000
Uh huh.
 
Uh huh.

460
00:41:07,000 --> 00:41:08,000
Û kîlok av.
 
And a kilo of water.

461
00:41:08,000 --> 00:41:10,000
Yanî emê ewa bikin.
 
Meaning we'll do this.

462
00:41:10,000 --> 00:41:12,000
Emê şerbetê xwe lê çêkin.
 
We will make our syrup.

463
00:41:12,000 --> 00:41:16,000
Kel vê ket, ewê kêrazê xwe têkinê.
 
Once it boils, we will add our cherries.

464
00:41:16,000 --> 00:41:19,000
Dê sê kela pêxînin...
 
We'll bring it to a boil three times...

465
00:41:19,000 --> 00:41:23,000
Û emê lê genî kin, ber rojê. Heftake ber rojê.
 
And we will leave it in the sun. For a week in the sun.

466
00:41:23,000 --> 00:41:25,000
Carekê, du caran têkvedin,
 
We stir it once or twice,

467
00:41:25,000 --> 00:41:28,000
Leçer çêdibe.
 
The leçer is done.

468
00:41:28,000 --> 00:41:29,000
Dema xwa ye?
 
Is it its season now?

469
00:41:29,000 --> 00:41:32,000
Ê, dema xwa ye biharê, wexta ji vira hate...
 
Yes, its season is in the spring, when it comes from over
here...

470
00:41:32,000 --> 00:41:33,000
Wîna çêkin.
 
You make it.

471
00:41:33,000 --> 00:41:38,000
Bes yê xwarinê nabe. Ev xususî darê gundî yê kêrazê heye.
 
But it's not the one for eating. This is a special cherry
tree from the village.

472
00:41:38,000 --> 00:41:40,000
Evê leçer heye.
 
It has this leçer.

473
00:41:40,000 --> 00:41:42,000
Mize.
 
It's sour.

474
00:41:42,000 --> 00:41:48,000
Û şerabê gundî jî, dîsa ew jî nefsî yê kêrazê...
 
And the village syrup as well, again it's the same as the
cherry one...

475
00:41:48,000 --> 00:41:52,000
Em diguvêşin, sîzakê dixin, mist didin...
 
We squeeze it, put it in a strainer, and press it...

476
00:41:52,000 --> 00:41:58,000
Şerbeta gundî, sê çar kîlo şikir, sê çar kîlo şerbeta
gundî...
 
Village syrup, three or four kilos of sugar, three or four
kilos of village syrup...

477
00:41:58,000 --> 00:42:00,000
Lê hev dixin.
 
We mix it together.

478
00:42:00,000 --> 00:42:04,000
Kelkê pê dixin, û didin ber rojê dîsa ew jî.
 
Bring it to a boil, and leave that in the sun again too.

479
00:42:04,000 --> 00:42:06,000
Ew jî dema xwa ye? Paşê wîna çêdikin?
 
Is that also in its season? Do you make it afterwards?

480
00:42:06,000 --> 00:42:09,000
Bi hefteyek çêdibe. Bi hefteyek çêdibe.
 
It's ready in a week. It's ready in a week.

481
00:42:09,000 --> 00:42:14,000
Û paşê ha vî leçerê kêrazo, hîn em dikin mûj jî... hişk
dikin, vayê leçer...
 
And then this cherry leçer, we also make it into a mûj... we
dry it, this leçer...

482
00:42:14,000 --> 00:42:16,000
Dikin mûj jî.
 
Make it into a mûj too.

483
00:42:16,000 --> 00:42:18,000
Mûjê xwa pir xwaş dibe.
 
Its mûj becomes very tasty.

484
00:42:18,000 --> 00:42:19,000
Um hum.
 
Um hum.

485
00:42:19,000 --> 00:42:21,000
Ev mûj hema nabin ba we ne?
 
Do you not have this mûj with you?

486
00:42:21,000 --> 00:42:25,000
Ê wallahî... nemane, zivistan xilas bûn, nemane.
 
Oh, by God... there's none left, it ran out in the winter,
there's none left.

487
00:42:25,000 --> 00:42:28,000
Em înşellah ji vira û wê de çêkin.
 
God willing, we will make it from here on out.

488
00:42:28,000 --> 00:42:30,000
Înşellah. Ev jî, te got şerab e?
 
God willing. This too, you said is syrup?

489
00:42:30,000 --> 00:42:32,000
Eva jî şerab e, erê.
 
This is also syrup, yes.

490
00:42:32,000 --> 00:42:35,000
Şeraba gundiye, îşte tirş dibe.
 
It's village syrup, you see it becomes sour.

491
00:42:35,000 --> 00:42:38,000
Em şerabê bitenê venaxwin, leçerê bitenê venaxwin...
 
We don't drink the syrup alone, we don't drink the leçer
alone...

492
00:42:38,000 --> 00:42:42,000
Vê dixin, paşî çêdikin pê avî, buzî çêdikin, vê dixin.
 
We put this in, then we prepare it with water and ice, we
put this in.

493
00:42:42,000 --> 00:42:43,000
Um hum.
 
Um hum.

494
00:42:43,000 --> 00:42:46,000
Yanî şûnê qazozê, şûnê çayê, şûnê ew qehwe...
 
I mean, instead of soda, instead of tea, instead of
coffee...

495
00:42:46,000 --> 00:42:51,000
Şûnê şerabê purteqalê de ra... yanî gîşka em ew dikin
îstîmal dikin.
 
Instead of orange juice... I mean, we use this for all of
them.

496
00:42:51,000 --> 00:42:54,000
Kanî dîkê ji me ra têk ve, em mîş bikin bibînin.
 
Well, pour some for us, let's taste it and see.

497
00:42:54,000 --> 00:43:14,000
Me têk ve ku, hun jî bibînin.
 
I'll pour it so you can see too.

498
00:43:22,000 --> 00:43:24,000
Piştî vê vîn avê têk ne?
 
After this, do you add water to it?

499
00:43:24,000 --> 00:43:26,000
Bûzê jî dikinê.
 
We add ice to it as well.

500
00:43:26,000 --> 00:43:46,000
Bûzê jî em dikinê.
 
We add ice to it as well.

501
00:44:09,000 --> 00:44:12,000
Ê bi rengê xwe jî, wexta we behs dikir we çêdikî...
 
Well, with its color too, as you were mentioning, you make
it...

502
00:44:12,000 --> 00:44:13,000
Em çêdikin.
 
We make it.

503
00:44:13,000 --> 00:44:14,000
Û vî rengî.
 
And this color.

504
00:44:14,000 --> 00:44:15,000
Ê vî rengî.
 
Yes, this color.

505
00:44:15,000 --> 00:44:20,000
Ji hefkê, sê fîtah be, keler sê kel vê keve, û ba rojê
yekşê.
 
From the jar, if it's open, it should boil three times, and
be in the sun for a week.

506
00:44:20,000 --> 00:44:24,000
Bi hefteyokê, xîlalî hefteyekê, leçer xelas dibe, digire
qewamê xwe digire.
 
In a week, over the course of a week, the leçer is finished,
it reaches its consistency.

507
00:44:24,000 --> 00:44:28,000
Û kêra-- ewê ji şerabê jî, tekî kela pê xînî,
 
And the cherr-- the syrup too, you just bring it to a boil,

508
00:44:28,000 --> 00:44:33,000
Çêkî û bidî ber rojêd, ew jî xilalî pêş şeş roja, ew jî têr
dibe,
 
Make it and leave it in the sun, over the course of five or
six days, that is ready too,

509
00:44:33,000 --> 00:44:42,000
Û digire qewamê xwe.
 
And it reaches its consistency.

510
00:44:42,000 --> 00:44:44,000
Belê temaşevanên hêja,
 
Yes, dear viewers,

511
00:44:44,000 --> 00:44:46,000
Li vir jî, em gihîştin dawiya bernameya xwe.
 
Here too, we have reached the end of our program.

512
00:44:46,000 --> 00:44:49,000
Îro jî, me gundê Me'reskê derbas kir.
 
Today too, we passed through the village of Me'reskê.

513
00:44:49,000 --> 00:44:53,000
Me hin der û dorê gundê Me'reskê nas kir, me taybetmendiyên
gund nas kir.
 
We got to know some of the surroundings of the village of
Me'reskê, we got to know the characteristics of the village.

514
00:44:53,000 --> 00:44:55,000
Lı vır jî, em xatirê xwe ji we dixwazin.
 
Here too, we bid you farewell.

515
00:44:55,000 --> 00:44:57,000
Heta hefteyeke din, em ê dîsa bi hev re bin.
 
Until next week, we will be together again.

516
00:44:57,000 --> 00:45:02,000
Hûn bimînin di nava xêr û xweşiyê da.
 
May you stay in goodness and well-being.

